        # ── IX. Discernment ──────────────────────────────────────────
        {
            "heading_zh": "九、关于分辨 ── 这是 Drash，不是 P'shat",
            "heading_en": "IX. A Word on Discernment — This is <em>Drash</em>, not <em>P'shat</em>",
            "body": [
                {"type": "p",
                 "zh": "如果这篇文章把拉比的每一句话都当作字面层次的预言应许，那将既不公平于他，也无益于读者。事实并非如此。把《弥迦书》七章 15 节的<em>niflaot</em>具体应用在「2026 年的中国家庭教会」——这是<em>drash</em>（דרש，讲道与启发层次的解经），不是字面的<em>p'shat</em>（פשט）。这是一个<strong>极具属灵份量的应用</strong>，但它仍是应用，不是字面的「这一节就是讲中国」。",
                 "en": "It would be unfair to Rabbi Shapira and unhelpful to readers to present every line of his teaching as a literal-level prophetic prediction. It is not. Applying Micah 7:15's <em>niflaot</em> specifically to “China's house churches in 2026” is <em>drash</em> (דרש, the homiletical/applicational layer of interpretation) — not <em>p'shat</em> (פשט, the plain reading). It is a <strong>spiritually weighty application</strong>, but it remains an application, not the literal sense “this verse is about China.”"},

                {"type": "p",
                 "zh": "同样，「约瑟余民」是弥赛亚犹太传统中一个有力但<em>建构性的</em>概念——不是一节单一经文的字面教义。<strong>聪明的读者要分辨：</strong>哪些是经文清楚说的（神要在末世显出 Exodus 式的奇事；外邦信徒是嫁接进橄榄树的；神有「列国中的义人」），哪些是拉比的<em>应用</em>（这正在中国发生；中国家庭教会正是约瑟脉络中的一支）。前者是经文，后者是受圣灵感动的应用——值得严肃考量，但不应等同于经文本身。",
                 "en": "Likewise, the “Joseph remnant” is a powerful but <em>constructive</em> concept within Messianic-Jewish tradition — not the literal doctrine of any one verse. <strong>Wise readers should distinguish:</strong> what the text plainly says (that God will display Exodus-style wonders in the last days, that Gentile believers are grafted into the olive tree, that God has His “righteous of the nations”) from the rabbi's <em>application</em> (that this is happening in China now, that the Chinese remnant stands on the Joseph line). The first is Scripture; the second is Spirit-led application — to be weighed seriously, but never collapsed into Scripture itself."},

                {"type": "p",
                 "zh": "但是——即使我们对每一个具体应用都保留谨慎——<em>那个更大的图景</em>仍然站立：神信实地在万国中工作；他对以色列的应许并未废去；他的奇事 (niflaot) 在末世必再次被显出；外邦人因信被嫁接进同一棵橄榄树。<strong>这个图景是经文本身的图景，不是推测。</strong>它在弥迦书里。它在罗马书里。它在我主耶书亚的事工里。",
                 "en": "And yet — even if we hold every specific application with appropriate caution — <em>the larger picture</em> still stands: God is faithful in His work among the nations; His promises to Israel are not annulled; His <em>niflaot</em> will be displayed again in the last days; Gentile believers are grafted by faith into the one olive tree. <strong>This larger picture is biblical, not speculative.</strong> It is in Micah. It is in Romans. It is in the ministry of our Lord Yeshua."},
            ],
        },

